const passport = require('passport');
const localStrategy = require('passport-local').Strategy;
const UserModel = require('../model/model');

passport.use(
  'signup',
  new localStrategy(
    {
      usernameField: 'email',
      passwordField: 'password'
    },
    async (email, password, done) => {
      try {
        const user = await UserModel.create({ email, password });

        return done(null, user);
      } catch (error) {
        done(error);
      }
    }
  )
);

passport.use(
  'login',
  new localStrategy(
    {
      usernameField: 'email',
      passwordField: 'password'
    },
    async (email, password, done) => {
      try {
        const user = await UserModel.findOne({ email });

        if (!user) {
          return done(null, false, { message: 'User not found' });
        }

        const validate = await user.isValidPassword(password);

        if (!validate) {
          return done(null, false, { message: 'Wrong Password' });
        }

        return done(null, user, { message: 'Logged in Successfully' });
      } catch (error) {
        return done(error);
      }
    }
  )
);



const JWTstrategy = require('passport-jwt').Strategy;
const ExtractJWT = require('passport-jwt').ExtractJwt;

passport.use(
  new JWTstrategy(
    {
      secretOrKey: 'TOP_SECRET',
      jwtFromRequest: ExtractJWT.fromUrlQueryParameter('secret_token')
    },
    async (token, done) => {
      try {
        return done(null, token.user);
      } catch (error) {
        done(error);
      }
    }
  )
);



const express = require('express');
const passport = require('passport');
const jwt = require('jsonwebtoken');

const router = express.Router();
router.post(
  '/signup',
  passport.authenticate('signup', { session: false }),
  async (req, res, next) => {
    res.json({
      message: 'Signup successful',
      user: req.user
    });
  }
);

router.post(
  '/login',
  async (req, res, next) => {
    passport.authenticate(
      'login',
      async (err, user, info) => {
        try {
          if (err || !user) {
            const error = new Error('An error occurred.');

            return next(error);
          }

          req.login(
            user,
            { session: false },
            async (error) => {
              if (error) return next(error);

              const body = { _id: user._id, email: user.email };
              const token = jwt.sign({ user: body }, 'TOP_SECRET');

              return res.json({ token });
            }
          );
        } catch (error) {
          return next(error);
        }
      }
    )(req, res, next);
  }
);


module.exports = router;



// test

      message: 'You made it to the secure route',
      user: req.user,
      token: req.query.secret_token
    })
  }
);

const mongoose = require('mongoose');
const bcrypt = require('bcrypt');

const Schema = mongoose.Schema;

const UserSchema = new Schema({
  email: {
    type: String,
    required: true,
    unique: true
  },
  password: {
    type: String,
    required: true
  }
});

UserSchema.pre(
  'save',
  async function(next) {
    const user = this;
    const hash = await bcrypt.hash(this.password, 10);

    this.password = hash;
    next();
  }
);

UserSchema.methods.isValidPassword = async function(password) {
  const user = this;
  const compare = await bcrypt.compare(password, user.password);

  return compare;
}

const UserModel = mongoose.model('user', UserSchema);

module.exports = UserModel;

    for (let index = 1; index < len; index += 2) {
        tempL.push(desc[index]);

    for (let index = 2; index < len; index += 2) {
        tempR.push(desc[index]);
    }
    for (let index = 0; index < tempR.length; index++) {
        temp[mid + index + 1] = tempR[index];
    }
    for (let index = 0; index < tempL.length; index++) {
        temp[mid - index - 1] = tempL[index];

        `computerSecurity`.`COURSE`

CREATE VIEW `computerSecurity`.`v2` AS
    SELECT 
        `computerSecurity`.`COURSE`.`cNum` AS `name`,
        `computerSecurity`.`COURSE_PREQ_GROUPS`.`preqGroupNum` AS `preqGroupNum`
    FROM
        (`computerSecurity`.`COURSE`
        JOIN `computerSecurity`.`COURSE_PREQ_GROUPS` ON ((`computerSecurity`.`COURSE`.`cNum` = `computerSecurity`.`COURSE_PREQ_GROUPS`.`cNum`)))

;

CREATE VIEW `computerSecurity`.`v3` AS
    SELECT 
        `v2`.`name` AS `name`,
        `computerSecurity`.`PREQ_GROUP_COURSES`.`cNum` AS `prerequisites`
    FROM
        (`computerSecurity`.`v2`
        JOIN `computerSecurity`.`PREQ_GROUP_COURSES` ON ((`v2`.`preqGroupNum` = `computerSecurity`.`PREQ_GROUP_COURSES`.`preqGroupNum`)))

;

CREATE VIEW `computerSecurity`.`v4` AS
    SELECT 
        `computerSecurity`.`PREQ_GROUP_COURSES`.`cNum` AS `COURSE`,
        COUNT(0) AS `numberOfTimes`
    FROM
        `computerSecurity`.`PREQ_GROUP_COURSES`
    GROUP BY `computerSecurity`.`PREQ_GROUP_COURSES`.`cNum`
    ORDER BY `numberOfTimes` DESC

;

CREATE VIEW `computerSecurity`.`v5` AS
    SELECT 
        `C`.`cNum` AS `COURSE`, 0 AS `numberofTimes`
    FROM
        `computerSecurity`.`COURSE` `C`
    WHERE
        (NOT (`C`.`cNum` IN (SELECT 
                `v4`.`COURSE`
            FROM
                `computerSecurity`.`v4`)))
;

CREATE VIEW `computerSecurity`.`v6` AS

        `v4`.`COURSE` AS `course`,
        `v4`.`numberOfTimes` AS `numberOfTimes`
    FROM
        `computerSecurity`.`v4`

        `v5`.`COURSE` AS `course`,
        `v5`.`numberofTimes` AS `numberofTimes`
    FROM
        `computerSecurity`.`v5`

CREATE VIEW `computerSecurity`.`v7` AS

        `v6`.`course` AS `course`,
        `v6`.`numberOfTimes` AS `numberofTimes`

    protected void manipulatePdf(String dest) throws Exception {
        //Initialize PDF writer
        PdfWriter writer = new PdfWriter(dest);
        //Initialize PDF document
        PdfDocument pdf = new PdfDocument(writer);
        //Initialize document
        Document document = new Document(pdf);
         document.setFontSize(10);
        //Add paragraph to the document
        Paragraph p = new Paragraph();
       
        p.setFixedLeading(0);
        document.add(p.add("RENTAL AGREEMENT FORM"));
       
        p = new Paragraph();
        p.setFixedLeading(0);
        document.add(p.add("HST Reg. No.\t:"+jTextField1.getText()));
        
        p = new Paragraph();
        p.setFixedLeading(0);
        document.add(p.add(jTextField2.getText()));

        
          p = new Paragraph();
        p.setFixedLeading(0);
        document.add(p.add(jTextField3.getText()));

        
        p = new Paragraph();
        p.setFixedLeading(0);
        document.add(p.add(jTextField4.getText()));

        
        
        
//        document.add(new Paragraph("PO No.\t"+jTextField2.getText()));
        //Close document
        document.close();
    }

#include<stdio.h>
#include<stdlib.h>

typedef struct node {
  int data;
  struct node *next;
} Node;

Node *insertToList(Node *head, int n);
Node * createNode(int n);
void printList(Node *head);
void freelist(Node *head);

int main()
{
  Node *head=NULL;
  int n, i;

  scanf("%d", &n);
  while (n>0) {
    head=insertToList(head, n);
    scanf("%d", &n);
  }
  printList(head);
  freelist(head);
}

/* Insert a record into the list headed by head. *
 * The list is maintained in ascending order     *
 * according to the data stored in the records   */
Node *insertToList(Node *head, int n)
{
  Node *p, *parent, *pn;

  if (head == NULL) {
    head = createNode(n);
    if (head == NULL) { 
      printf("not enough memory\n");
      exit(1);
    }
  }
  else { /* head != NULL */
    if (n <= head->data) { /* The new node should be the first on the list */
       pn = createNode(n);
       if (pn != NULL) {
          pn->next = head;
          head = pn;   
       }
       else {
          printf("not enough memory\n");
          freelist(head);
          exit(1);
       }
    } 
    else { /* The new node is not the first on the list */
       parent = head;
       p = parent->next;
       while ((p!=NULL) && (n > p->data)) {
          parent = p;
          p=p->next;
       }
       if (p!=NULL) { /* n <= p->data */
          pn = createNode(n);
          if (pn != NULL) {
             pn->next = p;
             parent->next = pn;
          }
          else {
             printf("Not enough memory\n");
             freelist(head);
             exit(1);
          }
       }
       else { /* When p==NULL, insert the node into the end of the list */
          pn = createNode(n);
          if (pn != NULL) 
             parent->next = pn;
          else {
             printf("Not enough memory\n");
             freelist(head);
             exit(1);
          } 
       }
    } 
  }
  return(head);
}

/* Create a node of type Node */
Node * createNode(int n)
{
  Node *p;
  
  p = (Node *)malloc(sizeof(Node));
  if (p == NULL)
     return(NULL);
  p->data = n;
  p->next = NULL;
  return(p);
}

/* Print to the standard output the integers *
 * stored in the list                        */
void printList(Node *head) 
{
  Node *p;
  if (head == NULL)
     printf("The list is empty\n");
  else {
    printf("The linked list is:\n");
    for (p=head; p!=NULL; p=p->next) {
       printf("%d-->", p->data);
    }
    printf("NULL\n");
  }
}

/* Free the memory space occupied by the *
 * list headed by head                   */ 
void freelist(Node *head)
{
  Node *p, *q;

  p = head;
  while (p!=NULL) {
    q = p->next;
    free(p);
    p = q;
  }
}

void swap(float *x, float *y) {
  float temp;

void bubbleSort(float *array, int size) {
  int i;
  int swapped;

  do {
    swapped = 0;
    for (i=0; i<size-1; i++)
      if (array[i]>array[i+1]) { 
         swap(&array[i], &array[i+1]); 
         swapped = 1;
      }
     size--;
   }
   while (swapped);

module LabM;
   reg [31:0] PCin;
   reg RegDst, RegWrite, clk, ALUSrc, MemRead, MemWrite, Mem2Reg;
   reg [2:0] op;
   wire [31:0] wd, rd1, rd2, imm, ins, PCp4, z, memOut, wb;
   wire [25:0] jTarget;
   wire zero;
   
   yIF myIF(ins, PCp4, PCin, clk);
   yID myID(rd1, rd2, imm, jTarget, ins, wd, RegDst, RegWrite, clk);
   yEX myEX(z, zero, rd1, rd2, imm, op, ALUSrc);
   yDM myDM(memOut, z, rd2, clk, MemRead, MemWrite);
   yWB myWB(wb, z, memOut, Mem2Reg);
   assign wd = wb;
   
   initial
      begin
         PCin = 128; clk = 0;
         repeat (11)
         begin
            clk = 1; #1;
            op = 3'b010;
            RegDst = 0; RegWrite = 0; ALUSrc = 1;
            MemRead = 0; MemWrite = 0; Mem2Reg = 0;
            if (ins[31:26] == 0)
               begin
                  RegDst = 1; RegWrite = 1; ALUSrc = 0; // All R-type ins
                  if (ins[5:0] == 37)
                     op = 3'b001; // intruction or
               end
            if (ins[31:26] == 4)
               begin
                  ALUSrc = 0; op = 3'b110; // intruction beq
               end
            if (ins[31:26] == 35)
               begin
                  RegWrite = 1; MemRead = 1; Mem2Reg = 1; // intruction lw
               end
            if (ins[31:26] == 43)
               MemWrite = 1; // inrtuction sw
            if (ins[31:26] == 8)
               RegWrite = 1; // intruction addi
            #1; clk = 0;
            $display("%h: rd1=%2d rd2=%2d z=%3d zero=%b wb=%2d",
               ins, rd1, rd2, z, zero, wb);
            //---------------------------------Prepare for the next ins
		if ((ins[31:26] == 4 && zero) == 1)
			PCin = PCp4 + (imm << 2) ;//shifted left twice;
		else if (ins[31:26] == 2)
			PCin = jTarget << 2;// shifted left twice;
		else
			PCin = PCp4;
         end
         $finish;
      end
endmodule
